ZH: 我今天早上睡了个懒觉。
EN: I slept in this morning.

ZH: 他喜欢每天都睡懒觉。
EN: He likes to sleep in every day.

ZH: 明天是周末，我计划睡个懒觉。
EN: Tomorrow is the weekend, and I plan to sleep in.

ZH: 她很少睡懒觉，总是早起。
EN: She rarely sleeps in and always wakes up early.

ZH: 昨天我刚好睡了一个懒觉，错过了早饭。
EN: I happened to sleep in yesterday and missed breakfast.

ZH: 在假期里，我可以每天都睡个懒觉。
EN: During the vacation, I can sleep in every day.

ZH: 我明白你想要睡个懒觉，但我们有个重要的约会。
EN: I understand you want to sleep in, but we have an important appointment.

ZH: 这台闹钟可以帮你不再睡懒觉。
EN: This alarm clock can help you stop sleeping in.

ZH: 他经常睡懒觉，导致上班迟到。
EN: He often sleeps in, which causes him to be late for work.

ZH: 睡过头是常常发生的，我都睡了个懒觉。
EN: Oversleeping happens often; I slept in.

ZH: 我今天早上放假，决定睡个懒觉。
EN: I have the day off today, so I decided to sleep in.

ZH: 对不起，我以为今天是周末，所以睡了个懒觉。
EN: Sorry, I thought today was the weekend, so I slept in.

ZH: 她每天都醒得很早，从来不睡懒觉。
EN: She wakes up early every day and never sleeps in.

ZH: 星期天是唯一允许自己睡懒觉的日子。
EN: Sunday is the only day I allow myself to sleep in.

ZH: 我昨天晚上很晚睡，今天就可以多睡一会懒觉。
EN: I slept late last night, so I can sleep in a bit today.

ZH: 别再睡懒觉了，快点起床吧！
EN: Stop sleeping in, get up quickly!

ZH: 他总是靠闹钟才能叫他起床，不然就睡个懒觉。
EN: He always relies on an alarm clock to wake him up; otherwise, he sleeps in.

ZH: 周末是我唯一能享受睡个懒觉的时间。
EN: The weekend is the only time I can enjoy sleeping in.

ZH: 我想为我的生日特别一点，可以睡懒觉吗？
EN: I want my birthday to be special; can I sleep in?

ZH: 你可以试着早点睡，就不会一直睡懒觉了。
EN: You can try going to bed earlier, so you won't constantly sleep in.
